A MAN was stabbed in a late night attack in the Gorbals.&nbsp;Police said the 27-year-old, who left a pub with three friends, was attacked following an altercation between him and a young man who approached the group.The victim was walking along Gorbals Street with his friends when they were approached by two young men and two young women in the early hours of Sunday.Police said there was an altercation between him and one of the other men, resulting in him receiving a stab wound.He was taken to the Victoria Infirmary where he is said to be stable.Police said the group continued up Gorbals Street, towards the Brazenhead Bar, after the incident.The suspect is said to be white, aged in his late teens or early 20s, and had a local accent. He wore a dark coloured puffa jacket.The other young man is described as white, in his late teens or early 20s with a thin build and wearing dark coloured clothing.The first young woman is described as white, late teens to early 20s, with a medium build and was wearing large spectacles. The other woman was white, late teens to early 20s with a thin build.Officers have been carrying out door-to-door enquiries in the area and looking at CCTV images.Detective Constable Mark Hendry said: &quot;This attack is completely random, there was some sort of altercation prior to the attack and we are in the process of establishing the exact circumstances around that, however a 27 year old man has been seriously assaulted with no clear motive when on a night out with friends and it's imperative we trace those responsible.&quot;This is a busy thoroughfare with many people either on foot or in cars or taxis - if you think you saw anything or have any knowledge of the crime or the suspects which could assist our investigation, please do get in touch.&quot;